# ============================================
# Vaani Web Environment Configuration
# ============================================

# API Server URL
# For development: http://localhost:5000
# For production: https://your-api-domain.com
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Google OAuth Client ID (REQUIRED)
# Get this from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 1. Create a new OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application type)
# 2. Add authorized JavaScript origins:
#    - http://localhost:5173 (development)
#    - https://your-domain.com (production)
# 3. Add authorized redirect URIs:
#    - http://localhost:5173 (development)
#    - https://your-domain.com (production)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id-here

# ============================================
# PRODUCTION SECURITY CHECKLIST
# ============================================
# [ ] Set VITE_API_URL to your production API URL
# [ ] Set VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID with production credentials
# [ ] Enable HTTPS on your hosting platform
# [ ] Consider using httpOnly cookies for token storage (requires backend support)
# [ ] Review Content Security Policy headers
# [ ] Enable session-only mode for high-security deployments:
#     Add to localStorage: vaani-session-mode = true
# ============================================
